laboratory_examinations.findings: Multiple gallstones with a trace amount of pericholecystic fluid. No gallbladder wall thickening or sonographic Murphy's sign. CBD not dilated, measuring at 6 mm.

Eighteen fluoroscopic images reviewed. Two surgical clips in gallbladder fossa. Cholangiogram showed no filling defects or strictures in the common bile duct. Intrahepatic biliary radicles appear normal.
